### Jack Turner: Introduction
- Relation of African traditions to Atlantic politics.
  - History of Political Philosophy, but black thinkers.
- Shoulders this book stands on: many have long insisted on the perspective of black writers and thinkers as essential.
- This collective history approach was selected because thinkers should be unified.
  - Prior ideas divide by ideology: black Marxism, black liberalism, black feminism, etc.
  - Allows us to tie these thinkers to broader movements, but reduces the individuality of black thinkers.
- A thinker-centered approach allows for a granular view of minds.
- This also allows for a breadth of study unallowed in a single-author volume.
  - Allows African American political thought and variety to be displayed.
  - Diversity of philosophical approach methods.
- Elaborating a thinker-centered approach automatically involves a second intervention: a reconstitution of US thought itself.
  - African American history is American history.
  - Studying slavery forces us to reconsider the sources of American values.
- American and African American history share a common root.
- Black history and US history are argued to be thought of as inseparable.

