### Conservative Black Voices
- Wonderful things that emphasizes the heterogeneity of African American political thought.
- Conservatism that runs through the chapters of Booker T. Washington and Clarence Thomas.
- Embedded in Washington's defense of economic self-help is a suspicion that white Americans are not up to treat black Americans on equal terms.
  - Engages in a series of deceptive maneuvers; very much the ideas of Marcus Garvey, Ida B. Wells, etc.
  - We see the volume as an instance to reimagining these figures and how terms we associate with them do not hap onto current politicla configurations.

